JavaScript Demos
Three interactive demos built with vanilla JavaScript, HTML, and CSS.
Live demos
Open `index.html` in any browser — no build step required.
Demos
1. Counter
Demonstrates closures, scope, and hoisting.
An IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression) wraps a private `count` variable
The returned object exposes `increment`, `decrement`, and `reset` — the only way to touch the state
Adjustable step size (1 / 5 / 10) shows how closures share private state
Key concepts: closure, IIFE, scope, encapsulation
---
2. To-do list
Demonstrates DOM manipulation and event handling.
Tasks stored in a plain array; every change re-renders the list via `innerHTML`
`addEventListener`-style inline handlers for checkbox toggle, delete, and filter
Filter buttons (All / Active / Done) use `Array.filter()` to derive the visible set
Input sanitised with a simple `escapeHtml` helper
Key concepts: DOM manipulation, event listeners, array methods (`map`, `filter`), immutable updates
---
3. Quiz
Demonstrates Promises and async/await.
`checkAnswer()` returns a `Promise` that resolves after 400 ms — simulating a real API call
The `pick()` function is declared `async` and uses `await` to wait for the result before updating the UI
Progress tracker shows completed / current / upcoming questions
Key concepts: `Promise`, `async/await`, asynchronous flow, DOM updates after async resolution
---
Acceptance criteria
Criterion	Where it's shown
Understands scope, closures, and hoisting	Counter — IIFE closure with private state
Can manipulate the DOM and handle events	To-do list — `innerHTML`, `onchange`, `onclick`
Built at least 2 small interactive demos	Counter + To-do + Quiz = 3 demos
Understands how Promises work	Quiz — `new Promise`, `async/await`
